data.title: FTX founder claims FTX was solvent, blamed lawyers for $136B enterprise destruction, had $16B equity, $8B withdrawal.
data.description: FTX founder Sam Bankman-Fried recently released a 15-page letter disputing claims of insolvency, stating that FTX's value was at $136 billion and blaming lawyers for causing the downfall. According to the document dated Sept. 30, Bankman-Fried highlighted that FTX and Alameda Research held $25 billion in assets and $16 billion in equity before facing a liquidity crisis in November 2022 due to $8 billion in withdrawal requests. He insisted that the company could have met creditor demands within weeks, if not for legal interference. Bankman-Fried accused FTX's bankruptcy team of misrepresenting the situation and unnecessary Chapter 11 filing, alleging they had enough assets to cover debts. The founder argued that legal actions had severely impacted the company's financial standing.

data.title: ResMed (NYSE: RMD) beats Q1 earnings with $2.55 EPS, exceeding $1.336B sales. CEO Farrell announces strong fiscal start.
data.description: ResMed Inc. (NYSE: RMD) exceeded expectations in the first quarter, reporting earnings of $2.55 per share compared to the analyst estimate of $2.50 per share. The company also surpassed sales estimates with quarterly revenues reaching $1.336 billion, exceeding the anticipated $1.331 billion. Resmed's Chairman and CEO, Mick Farrell, highlighted the strong start to fiscal year 2026, emphasizing the company's dedication to improving sleep quality and overall health through in-home care. Additionally, ResMed achieved a 9% increase in headline growth. More details can be found on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Global Directory of Distilleries 2025 offers info on thousands of distilleries in 150 countries, with comprehensive data on addresses, contact details, parent companies, and production capacities - ResearchAndMarkets.com.
data.description: A new directory named "Global Directory of Distilleries 2025" has recently been included in the offerings of ResearchAndMarkets.com. This comprehensive directory covers thousands of distilleries across 150 countries globally. It offers extensive details on company addresses, telephone numbers, email addresses, website contacts, parent companies, contact persons with titles, feedstocks used, product types, brand names, and production capacities. data.title: Teledyne completes acquisition of TransponderTech from Saab, forming Teledyne FLIR TransponderTech AB in Sweden.
data.description: In Thousand Oaks, California, Teledyne Technologies Incorporated (NYSE:TDY) completed the acquisition of TransponderTech business from Saab AB. The acquisition resulted in the formation of Teledyne FLIR TransponderTech AB, adding to Teledyne’s portfolio alongside Raymarine, FLIR Marine, ChartWorld, and Teledyne CARIS brands. The new entity is based in Linköping, Sweden, expanding Teledyne's maritime technology solutions. This move signifies the growth and diversification of Teledyne in the industry.
